org.eclipse.emf.compare.match.util
Class MatchAdapterFactory

java.lang.Object
  AdapterFactoryImpl
      org.eclipse.emf.compare.match.util.MatchAdapterFactory

public class MatchAdapterFactory
extends AdapterFactoryImpl

The Adapter Factory for the model. It provides an adapter createXXX method for each class of the model.

isFactoryForType

public boolean isFactoryForType(java.lang.Object object)
Returns whether this factory is applicable for the type of the object. This implementation returns true if the object is either the model's package or is an instance object of the model.

Returns:
whether this factory is applicable for the type of the object.

createMatchModelAdapter

public Adapter createMatchModelAdapter()
Creates a new adapter for an object of class 'Model'. This default implementation returns null so that we can easily ignore cases; it's useful to ignore a case when inheritance will catch all the cases anyway.

Returns:
the new adapter.
